summary: This document provides detailed information on how to view aircraft records, including the types of files contained on a CD Rom, the sequence of document display, and the types of documents related to airworthiness and registration. It also explains the numbering system for documents and the use of bookmarks in the Acrobat Reader for navigating the records.
keyFacts: The document outlines the structure and content of aircraft records available on CD Rom.
It describes the types of files included, such as Airworthiness, Registration, and Suspense files.
The document explains the numbering system for documents and how they are displayed in the Acrobat Reader.
